                    "node_type": "interp", 
                    "text": "1. Secured by new manufactured home and land\u2014physical visit of the interior. A transaction secured by a new manufactured home and land is subject to the requirements of \u00a7 1026.35(c)(3) through (6) except for the requirement in \u00a7 1026.35(c)(3)(i) that the appraiser conduct a physical inspection of the interior of the property. Thus, for example, a creditor of a loan secured by a new manufactured home and land could comply with \u00a7 1026.35(c)(3)(i) by obtaining an appraisal conducted by a state-certified or -licensed appraiser based on plans and specifications for the new manufactured home and an inspection of the land on which the property will be sited, as well as any other information necessary for the appraiser to complete the appraisal assignment in conformity with the Uniform Standards of Professional Appraisal Practice and the requirements of FIRREA and any implementing regulations."
