                            "paragraphs": [
                                "For applications received on or after July 18, 2015, new rules will apply to loans secured by manufactured homes, as follows:", 
                                "(1) The temporary exemption for loans secured by existing manufactured homes and land will expire; those loans will be subject to the HPML appraisal rules in \u00a7 1026.35(c)(3) through (6).", 
                                "(2) A modified exemption for loans secured by a new manufactured home and land will take effect; those loans will be subject to all of the HPML appraisal requirements except the requirement that the appraisal include a physical visit of the interior of the property. <em data-original=\"E-03\">See</em> &#167; 1026.35(c)(2)(viii)(A) and accompanying section-by-section analysis.", 
                                "(3) An exemption for loans secured by either a new or existing manufactured home and not land will be subject to a condition that the creditor obtain and provide to the consumer one of three types of value-related information. <em data-original=\"E-03\">See</em> &#167; 1026.35(c)(2)(viii)(B) and accompanying section-by-section analysis.", 
                                "These new rules are discussed below."
